Variables & Data Tracking (submit it during week 1)– Discuss the types of variables you used, why different variables were needed. 
Selection Structure – Identify where you used control structures and explain what problem the decision solved in your game.
Repetition Structure – Choose one loop implementation and explain its purpose and how it works.
Arrays & Data Structures – Provide array snippet(s) and explain how you store multiple items, how you access them, and how they support your program.
Use of Custom Functions & Error Checking/Restrictions – Select a couple of key methods you wrote, explain their purpose and how they support the game, and describe any error checking or restrictions built into your program.
Each entry should include:

What concept (from the list above) did you implement? State the topic clearly and include a relevant code snippet.
Where did you use it, and why did you implement it that way? Explain the purpose of the code and your reasoning behind the approach you chose.
What challenges did you encounter, and how did you fix them? Describe any issues you faced and the steps you took to resolve them.



